{"title_page": "Alexandre D'Acol", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n | name                = Alexandre D'Acol\n | image                =\n | caption              = \n | birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|7|18}}\n | birth_place = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]]\n | height               = {{convert|1.86|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n | position             = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Forward]] / [[Attacking midfielder]]\n | currentclub          =\n | clubnumber           =\n | youthyears1          = \u20132004\n | youthclubs1          = Comercial\n | youthyears2          = 2001\u20132002\n | youthclubs2          = \u2192 [[Esporte Clube Vit\u00f3ria|Vit\u00f3ria]] (loan)\n | years1   = 2004\u20132007 | caps1 = 10 | goals1 = 0  | clubs1 = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n | years2   = 2006\u20132007 | caps2 = 22 | goals2 = 4  | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Kerkyra F.C.|Kerkyra]] (loan)\n | years3   = 2007\u20132009 | caps3 = 2  | goals3 = 0  | clubs3 = [[Panionios G.S.S.|Panionios]]\n | years4   = 2010\u20132011 | caps4 = 26 | goals4 = 13 | clubs4 = [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]\n | years5   = 2011\u20132012 | caps5 = 22 | goals5 = 11 | clubs5 = [[Thrasyvoulos F.C.|Thrasyvoulos]]\n | years6   = 2012\u20132013 | caps6 = 39 | goals6 = 25 | clubs6 = [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]\n | years7   = 2013\u20132015 | caps7 = 37 | goals7 = 25 | clubs7 = [[AEK F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n | years8   = 2015\u20132017 | caps8 = 44 | goals8 = 9  | clubs8 = [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical]]\n | years9   = 2017      | caps9 = 3  | goals9 = 0  | clubs9 = [[PAS Lamia 1964|Lamia]]\n| years10   = 2018      | caps10 = 7 | goals10 = 0 | clubs10 = [[Trikala F.C.|Trikala]]\n | pcupdate =  7 March 2018 \n | ntupdate = \n}}\n\n'''Alexandre D'Acol Joaquim''' (born 18 July 1986) is a [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], D'Acol began playing professional football for local side Comercial Futebol Clube (S\u00e3o Paulo). He had a loan spell with [[Esporte Clube Vit\u00f3ria]],<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Kerkyra F.C. |title=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03ad\u03c1\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bf Dacol |url=http://www.aokerkyra.gr/readnew.php?aa=70 |language=Greek |date=11 January 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120426065757/http://www.aokerkyra.gr/readnew.php?aa=70 |archivedate=26 April 2012 }}</ref> and would join [[Greek Superleague]] side [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] in August 2004.<ref>[http://www2.cbf.com.br/bid/ti2004.htm RELAT\u00d3RIO DE TRANSFER\u00caNCIAS INTERNACIONAIS EM 2004] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100402225550/http://www.cbf.com.br/bid/ti2004.htm |date=2 April 2010 }}</ref>\n\n===Career in Greece===\nOlympiacos send D'Acol on a one-year loan to [[Kerkyra F.C.|Kerkyra]] in 2006 and again in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|work=The Guardian |location=UK |title=Stats Centre: Alexandre Joaquim D'Acol Facts |url=http://guardian.touch-line.com/StatsCentre.asp?CTID=31&CPID=76&TEID=682&PLID=187727&pStr=Player |accessdate=17 August 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120726163311/http://guardian.touch-line.com/StatsCentre.asp?CTID=31&CPID=76&TEID=682&PLID=187727&pStr=Player |archivedate=26 July 2012 }}</ref>\nWhile in [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]] D'Acol made his way to be one of the top goal-scorers in both the Greek Football League (Second Professional League) and the Greek Cup.\nIn 2013, [[AEK F.C.|AEK Athens]] signed D'Acol for two years. In his first appearance with AEK's jersey (friendly match, 31 August 2013), he scored a goal against his previous team, Kallithea.<ref>{{cite web|work=aek365 |location=Greece| language=Greek| title= Post Match: Kallithea - AEK Athens |url=http://www.aek365.com/a-287867/kallithea-aek-live.htm|accessdate=31 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Hamilton Academical===\nOn 26 August 2015, D'Acol joined [[Scottish Premiership]] side [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical]] on a one-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/accies-sign-striker-d039acol/ |title=Accies sign striker D'Acol |work=spfl.co.uk |publisher=Scottish Professional Football League |date=26 August 2015 |accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref> On 27 June 2016, he signed a new contract, keeping him at the club for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hamilton hand striker Alexandre D'Acol one-year deal|url=http://www.eveningtimes.co.uk/sport/other_football/14582638.Hamilton_hand_striker_Alexandre_D_Acol_one_year_deal/|work=Evening Times|last=Mackenzie|first=Alasdair|date=27 June 2016|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Return to Greece===\nOn 11 September 2017, just before the end of the transfer window, [[Lamia F.C.|Lamia]] announced the signing of the Brazilian striker.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Lamia/epishmo-sth-lamia-ntakol-kai-krisantoys.4841474.html |title=\u0395\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039b\u03b1\u03bc\u03af\u03b1 \u039d\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bb \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039a\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03ac\u03bd\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 |publisher=sport24.gr |date=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 19 December 2017, after some poor performances, the club announced that D'Acol's contract had been terminated.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Lamia/telos-kai-o-ntakol-apo-lamia.4994106.html |title=\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf \u039d\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bb \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u039b\u03b1\u03bc\u03af\u03b1 |publisher=sport24.gr |date=19 December 2017}}</ref> On 1 January 2018, he signed a contract with [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]] club [[Trikala F.C.]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{soccerbase|id=87742|name=Alexandre D'Acol}}\n* {{Soccerway}}\n*[http://www.onsports.gr/onstats/?url=/soccer/player/main.php&sport-select=soccer&player-select=1912 Onsports Profile]\n*[http://www.epae.org/player.fds?categ=2&team=44&player=9007&pagecode=04&langid=1 Profile] at EPAE.org\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:D'Acol, Alexandre}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Olympiacos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:PAE Kerkyra players]]\n[[Category:Panionios F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kallithea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Thrasyvoulos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AEK Athens F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hamilton Academical F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Professional Football League players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Scotland]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n | name                = Alexandre D'Acol\n | image                =\n | caption              = \n | birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|7|18}}\n | birth_place = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]]\n | height               = {{convert|1.86|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n | position             = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Forward]] / [[Attacking midfielder]]\n | currentclub          =\n | clubnumber           =\n | youthyears1          = \u20132004\n | youthclubs1          = Comercial\n | youthyears2          = 2001\u20132002\n | youthclubs2          = \u2192 [[Esporte Clube Vit\u00f3ria|Vit\u00f3ria]] (loan)\n | years1   = 2004\u20132007 | caps1 = 10 | goals1 = 0  | clubs1 = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n | years2   = 2006\u20132007 | caps2 = 22 | goals2 = 4  | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Kerkyra F.C.|Kerkyra]] (loan)\n | years3   = 2007\u20132009 | caps3 = 2  | goals3 = 0  | clubs3 = [[Panionios G.S.S.|Panionios]]\n | years4   = 2010\u20132011 | caps4 = 26 | goals4 = 13 | clubs4 = [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]\n | years5   = 2011\u20132012 | caps5 = 22 | goals5 = 11 | clubs5 = [[Thrasyvoulos F.C.|Thrasyvoulos]]\n | years6   = 2012\u20132013 | caps6 = 39 | goals6 = 25 | clubs6 = [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]]\n | years7   = 2013\u20132015 | caps7 = 37 | goals7 = 25 | clubs7 = [[AEK F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n | years8   = 2015\u20132017 | caps8 = 44 | goals8 = 9  | clubs8 = [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical]]\n | years9   = 2017      | caps9 = 3  | goals9 = 0  | clubs9 = [[PAS Lamia 1964|Lamia]]\n| years10   = 2018      | caps10 = 7 | goals10 = 0 | clubs10 = [[Trikala F.C.|Trikala]]\n | pcupdate =  7 March 2018 \n | ntupdate = \n}}\n\n \n'''Alexandre D'Acol Joaquim''' (born 18 July 1986) is a [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], D'Acol began playing professional football for local side Comercial Futebol Clube (S\u00e3o Paulo). He had a loan spell with [[Esporte Clube Vit\u00f3ria]],<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Kerkyra F.C. |title=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03ad\u03c1\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bf Dacol |url=http://www.aokerkyra.gr/readnew.php?aa=70 |language=Greek |date=11 January 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120426065757/http://www.aokerkyra.gr/readnew.php?aa=70 |archivedate=26 April 2012 }}</ref> and would join [[Greek Superleague]] side [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] in August 2004.<ref>[http://www2.cbf.com.br/bid/ti2004.htm RELAT\u00d3RIO DE TRANSFER\u00caNCIAS INTERNACIONAIS EM 2004] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100402225550/http://www.cbf.com.br/bid/ti2004.htm |date=2 April 2010 }}</ref>\n\n===Career in Greece===\nOlympiacos send D'Acol on a one-year loan to [[Kerkyra F.C.|Kerkyra]] in 2006 and again in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|work=The Guardian |location=UK |title=Stats Centre: Alexandre Joaquim D'Acol Facts |url=http://guardian.touch-line.com/StatsCentre.asp?CTID=31&CPID=76&TEID=682&PLID=187727&pStr=Player |accessdate=17 August 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120726163311/http://guardian.touch-line.com/StatsCentre.asp?CTID=31&CPID=76&TEID=682&PLID=187727&pStr=Player |archivedate=26 July 2012 }}</ref>\nWhile in [[Kallithea F.C.|Kallithea]] D'Acol made his way to be one of the top goal-scorers in both the Greek Football League (Second Professional League) and the Greek Cup.\nIn 2013, [[AEK F.C.|AEK Athens]] signed D'Acol for two years. In his first appearance with AEK's jersey (friendly match, 31 August 2013), he scored a goal against his previous team, Kallithea.<ref>{{cite web|work=aek365 |location=Greece| language=Greek| title= Post Match: Kallithea - AEK Athens |url=http://www.aek365.com/a-287867/kallithea-aek-live.htm|accessdate=31 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Hamilton Academical===\nOn 26 August 2015, D'Acol joined [[Scottish Premiership]] side [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical]] on a one-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/accies-sign-striker-d039acol/ |title=Accies sign striker D'Acol |work=spfl.co.uk |publisher=Scottish Professional Football League |date=26 August 2015 |accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref> On 27 June 2016, he signed a new contract, keeping him at the club for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hamilton hand striker Alexandre D'Acol one-year deal|url=http://www.eveningtimes.co.uk/sport/other_football/14582638.Hamilton_hand_striker_Alexandre_D_Acol_one_year_deal/|work=Evening Times|last=Mackenzie|first=Alasdair|date=27 June 2016|accessdate=9 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Return to Greece===\nOn 11 September 2017, just before the end of the transfer window, [[Lamia F.C.|Lamia]] announced the signing of the Brazilian striker.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Lamia/epishmo-sth-lamia-ntakol-kai-krisantoys.4841474.html |title=\u0395\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039b\u03b1\u03bc\u03af\u03b1 \u039d\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bb \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039a\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03ac\u03bd\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 |publisher=sport24.gr |date=11 September 2017}}</ref> On 19 December 2017, after some poor performances, the club announced that D'Acol's contract had been terminated.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Lamia/telos-kai-o-ntakol-apo-lamia.4994106.html |title=\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf \u039d\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bb \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u039b\u03b1\u03bc\u03af\u03b1 |publisher=sport24.gr |date=19 December 2017}}</ref> On 1 January 2018, he signed a contract with [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]] club [[Trikala F.C.]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{soccerbase|id=87742|name=Alexandre D'Acol}}\n*[http://www.scoresway.com/?sport=soccer&page=player&id=155120 Scoresway.com Profile]\n*[http://www.onsports.gr/onstats/?url=/soccer/player/main.php&sport-select=soccer&player-select=1912 Onsports Profile]\n*[http://www.epae.org/player.fds?categ=2&team=44&player=9007&pagecode=04&langid=1 Profile] at EPAE.org\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:D'Acol, Alexandre}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Olympiacos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:PAE Kerkyra players]]\n[[Category:Panionios F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kallithea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Thrasyvoulos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AEK Athens F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hamilton Academical F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Professional Football League players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Scotland]]\n", "name_user": "Pelmeen10", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexandre_D%27Acol"}
{"title_page": "Dimitris Sounas", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n|                name = Dimitris Sounas\n|               image = \n|            fullname = Dimitrios Sounas\n|              height = {{height|m=1.77}}\n|          birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1994|08|12}}\n|         birth_place = [[Moudania, Greece|Portaria]], [[Chalkidiki]], Greece\n|         currentclub = [[Reggina 1914|Reggina]]\n|          clubnumber = 7\n|            position = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = 2010\u20132011 | youthclubs1 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132015 | clubs1 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]        | caps1 = 36 | goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2016      | clubs2 = [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]]| caps2 = 13 | goals2 = 0   \n| years3 = 2016\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[S.S. Monopoli 1966|Monopoli]]        | caps3 = 86 | goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 2019\u2013     | clubs4 = [[Reggina 1914|Reggina]]               | caps4 = 4 | goals4 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013 | nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U-19]] | nationalcaps1  = 8 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2015      | nationalteam2 = [[Greece national under-21 football team|Greece U-21]] | nationalcaps2  = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0\n| pcupdate = 16 September 2019\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n\n'''Dimitris Sounas''' ({{lang-gr|\u0394\u03b7\u03bc\u03ae\u03c4\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2}}; born on 12 August 1994)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arisfc.gr/gr/%CE%B4%CE%B7%CE%BC%CE%AE%CF%84%CF%81%CE%B7%CF%82-%CF%83%CE%BF%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AC%CF%82-%28grc%29.html |accessdate=27 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120818201451/http://www.arisfc.gr/gr/%CE%B4%CE%B7%CE%BC%CE%AE%CF%84%CF%81%CE%B7%CF%82-%CF%83%CE%BF%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AC%CF%82-%28grc%29.html |archivedate=18 August 2012 |title=Dimitris Sounas |df=dmy-all }}</ref> is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Serie C]] club [[Reggina 1914|Reggina]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Aris===\nHe started his career in youth teams of Aris. In 2012, new head coach [[Makis Katsavakis]] promoted him to the first team, and he made his debut on 14 August 2012, in a friendly game against [[Veria F.C.|Veria]] scoring a goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Aris/soynas_apisteyto_to_synaisthhma.1892202.html |title=\u03a3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2: \u0391\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03af\u03c3\u03b8\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 - \u039d\u03ad\u03b1, \u039f\u03bc\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2, \u03a0\u03c1\u03cc\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03bc\u03bc\u03b1, \u0391\u03c0\u03bf\u03c4\u03b5\u03bb\u03ad\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1, \u0392\u03b1\u03b8\u03bc\u03bf\u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03af\u03b5\u03c2, \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac - SPORT 24 |language=el |publisher=Sport24.gr |date= |accessdate=2012-09-29}}</ref> From August 2012 he is also member of [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece's U19 national team]] after he was chosen from Kostas Tsanas, head of the U19 team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athlitikanea.gr/index.php/%CE%A0%CE%9F%CE%94%CE%9F%CE%A3%CE%A6%CE%91%CE%99%CE%A1%CE%9F/Super-League/%CE%91%CE%A1%CE%97%CE%A3/%CE%A3%CE%BF%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AC%CF%82-%CE%BA%CE%B1%CE%B9-%CE%91%CE%BD%CF%84%CF%89%CE%BD%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%B4%CE%B7%CF%82-%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B7%CE%BD-%CE%95%CE%B8%CE%BD%CE%B9%CE%BA%CE%AE-%CE%9D%CE%AD%CF%89%CE%BD.html|title=\u03a3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0391\u03bd\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd\u03b9\u03ac\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u039d\u03ad\u03c9\u03bd|publisher=Athlitikanea.gr|accessdate=2012-09-29|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120818190930/http://www.athlitikanea.gr/index.php/%CE%A0%CE%9F%CE%94%CE%9F%CE%A3%CE%A6%CE%91%CE%99%CE%A1%CE%9F/Super-League/%CE%91%CE%A1%CE%97%CE%A3/%CE%A3%CE%BF%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AC%CF%82-%CE%BA%CE%B1%CE%B9-%CE%91%CE%BD%CF%84%CF%89%CE%BD%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%B4%CE%B7%CF%82-%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B7%CE%BD-%CE%95%CE%B8%CE%BD%CE%B9%CE%BA%CE%AE-%CE%9D%CE%AD%CF%89%CE%BD.html|archivedate=18 August 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> His professional debut was made on 27 August 2012 against [[Panionios G.S.S.|Panionios]] and his first goal against [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]] in [[Kleanthis Vikelidis Stadium|Kleanthis Vikelidis]] in a 1-1 draw. On 23 September 2015, he dissolved his contract with the club.\n\n===Apollon Smyrnis===\nAfter 3 years in Aris, Sounas signed as a free agent, to play with [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]] in the [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]] till the end of the [[2016-17 Football League (Greece)|2016-17 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport-fm.gr/article/podosfairo/anakoinwthike-kai-paizei-o-sounas/3135345 |accessdate=15 January 2016 |title= \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03ce\u03b8\u03b7\u03ba\u03b5 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c0\u03b1\u03af\u03b6\u03b5\u03b9 \u03bf \u03a3\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd\u03b1\u03c2|publisher= www.sport-fm.gr}}</ref>\n\n===Monopoli===\nOn 17 July 2016, Sounas has signed a contract with [[Lega Pro]] club [[S.S. Monopoli 1966|Monopoli]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/EllinesExoterikou/sthn-monopoli-1966-ths-italias-oi-soynas-moyzakiths.4174940.html |accessdate=17 July 2016 |title= \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd Monopoli \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0399\u03c4\u03b1\u03bb\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03a3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2, \u039c\u03bf\u03c5\u03b6\u03b1\u03ba\u03af\u03c4\u03b7\u03c2|publisher= www.sport24.gr}}</ref> He left the club having 93 appearances (4 goals, 17 assists) in all competitions.\n\n===Reggina===\nOn 2 July 2019, Sounas has signed a contract with [[Lega Pro]] club [[Reggina 1914|Reggina]] until the summer of 2021 with an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.citynow.it/reggina-ufficiale-dimitrios-sounas/ |accessdate=2 July 2019 |title= Reggina, ufficiale Dimitrios Sounas|publisher= www.citynow.it}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:88%; text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=2|Championship\n!colspan=2|Cup\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |[[Aris F.C. (Thessaloniki)|Aris]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Superleague Greece|2012\u201313]]\n|18||1||2||1||0||0||20||2\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Superleague Greece|2013\u201314]]\n|18||0||2||0||0||0||20||0\n|-\n| rowspan=1 |[[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Football League (Greece)|2015\u201316]]\n|13||0||0||0||0||0||13||0\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |[[S.S. Monopoli 1966|Monopoli]]\n|[[2016\u201317 Lega Pro|2016\u201317]]\n|26||0||0||0||0||0||26||0\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Lega Pro|2017\u201318]]\n|35||3||0||0||0||0||35||3\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Lega Pro|2018\u201319]]\n|25||1||2||0||0||0||27||1\n|-\n| rowspan=1 |[[Reggina 1914|Reggina]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Serie C|2019\u201320]]\n|4||1||2||0||0||0||6||1\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Total\n!139!!6!!8!!1!!0!!0!!147!!7\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway}}\n*[https://archive.is/20131130172051/http://guardian.touch-line.com/statscentre.asp?Lang=0&CTID=31&CPID=76&pStr=Player&PLID=233701&TEID=673 Player info @ Guardian.touch-line.com]\n\n{{Urbs Reggina 1914 squad}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sounas, Dimitris}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:People from Chalkidiki]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Greek footballers]]\n[[Category:Greece youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Greece under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Aris Thessaloniki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Apollon Smyrni F.C. players]]\n[[Category:S.S. Monopoli 1966 players]]\n[[Category:Reggina 1914 players]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:Football League (Greece) players]]\n[[Category:Serie C players]]\n[[Category:Greek expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|                name = Dimitris Sounas\n|               image = \n|            fullname = Dimitrios Sounas\n|              height = {{height|m=1.77}}\n|          birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1994|08|12}}\n|         birth_place = [[Moudania, Greece|Portaria]], [[Chalkidiki]], Greece\n|         currentclub = [[Reggina 1914|Reggina]]\n|          clubnumber = 7\n|            position = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = 2010\u20132011 | youthclubs1 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132015 | clubs1 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]        | caps1 = 36 | goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2016      | clubs2 = [[Apollon Smyrni F.C.|Apollon Smyrnis]]| caps2 = 13 | goals2 = 0   \n| years3 = 2016\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[S.S. Monopoli 1966|Monopoli]]        | caps3 = 86 | goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 2019\u2013     | clubs4 = [[Reggina 1914|Reggina]]               | caps4 = 4 | goals4 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013 | nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U-19]] | nationalcaps1  = 8 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2015      | nationalteam2 = [[Greece national under-21 football team|Greece U-21]] | nationalcaps2  = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0\n| pcupdate = 16 September 2019\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n\n'''Dimitris Sounas''' ({{lang-gr|\u0394\u03b7\u03bc\u03ae\u03c4\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2}}; born on 12 August 1994)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arisfc.gr/gr/%CE%B4%CE%B7%CE%BC%CE%AE%CF%84%CF%81%CE%B7%CF%82-%CF%83%CE%BF%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AC%CF%82-%28grc%29.html |accessdate=27 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120818201451/http://www.arisfc.gr/gr/%CE%B4%CE%B7%CE%BC%CE%AE%CF%84%CF%81%CE%B7%CF%82-%CF%83%CE%BF%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AC%CF%82-%28grc%29.html |archivedate=18 August 2012 |title=Dimitris Sounas |df=dmy-all }}</ref> is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Serie C]] club [[Reggina 1914|Reggina]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Aris===\nHe started his career in youth teams of Aris. In 2012, new head coach [[Makis Katsavakis]] promoted him to the first team, and he made his debut on 14 August 2012, in a friendly game against [[Veria F.C.|Veria]] scoring a goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Aris/soynas_apisteyto_to_synaisthhma.1892202.html |title=\u03a3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2: \u0391\u03c0\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03af\u03c3\u03b8\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 - \u039d\u03ad\u03b1, \u039f\u03bc\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2, \u03a0\u03c1\u03cc\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03bc\u03bc\u03b1, \u0391\u03c0\u03bf\u03c4\u03b5\u03bb\u03ad\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1, \u0392\u03b1\u03b8\u03bc\u03bf\u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03af\u03b5\u03c2, \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac - SPORT 24 |language=el |publisher=Sport24.gr |date= |accessdate=2012-09-29}}</ref> From August 2012 he is also member of [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece's U19 national team]] after he was chosen from Kostas Tsanas, head of the U19 team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athlitikanea.gr/index.php/%CE%A0%CE%9F%CE%94%CE%9F%CE%A3%CE%A6%CE%91%CE%99%CE%A1%CE%9F/Super-League/%CE%91%CE%A1%CE%97%CE%A3/%CE%A3%CE%BF%CF%85%CE%BD%CE%AC%CF%82-%CE%BA%CE%B1%CE%B9-%CE%91%CE%BD%CF%84%CF%89%CE%BD%CE%B9%CE%AC%CE%B4%CE%B7%CF%82-%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B7%CE%BD-%CE%95%CE%B8%CE%BD%CE%B9%CE%BA%CE%AE-%CE%9D%CE%AD%CF%89%CE%BD.html|title=\u03a3\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd\u03ac\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0391\u03bd\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd\u03b9\u03ac\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u039d\u03ad\u03c9\u03bd|publisher=Athlitikanea.gr|accessdate=2012-09-29|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120818190930/http://www.athlitikanea.gr/