in completes Bournemouth deal | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/15652339 | work = BBC Sport | accessdate = 12 February 2013 |date = 9 November 2011}}</ref>{{flagicon|USA}} PEAK6 Investments (25%)<ref>{{cite news | title = AFC Bournemouth owner Maxim Demin sells 25 per cent stake to US private equity firm |author1=Jeremy Wilson | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2016/02/05/afc-bournemouth-owner-maxim-demin-sells-25-per-cent-stake-to-us/}}</ref>\n|$110M<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/markets/ipos/company/peak6-corp-85132-12680?tab=financials|title=PEAK6 CORP IPO|website=NASDAQ.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-07-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.walesonline.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/every-premier-league-owners-net-15174267|title=Every Premier League owner's worth and where Vincent Tan ranks|last=Booth|first=Dominic|date=2018-09-20|website=walesonline|access-date=2019-07-14}}</ref>\n|[[Petrochemicals]] trading<br />Seven Developments\nInvestments\n|-\n|[[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tony Bloom]] (75.61%)<ref name=\"FourFourTwo\">{{cite news | title = The Football Rich List 2011/12: The Full 100  | url = http://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/football-rich-list-201112-full-100| archivedate=24 December 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224121322/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/football-rich-list-201112-full-100|work = Four Four Two| accessdate = 13 February 2013}}</ref>\n|{{sort|12|$1.7B}}\n|Online Gambling, Real Estate, Property, Land Development & Investments\n|-\n|[[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} Mike Garlick (49.3%)<br />{{flagicon|ENG}} John Banaszkiewicz (27.55%)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/club/boardroom/|title=Board of Directors/CEO|work=Burnley F.C.|accessdate=9 May 2014}}</ref>\n|{{sort|18|$100M}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hertfordshirelife.co.uk/home/the_rich_list_2014_1_3511555|title=The Rich List 2014|w