zer ownership of Manchester United|The Glazer Family]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.manutd.com/en/Club/FAQs/Club-Ownership/Question-1.aspx |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110315195813/http://www.manutd.com/en/Club/FAQs/Club-Ownership/Question-1.aspx |url-status=dead |archive-date=15 March 2011 |title=Who owns the club? |work=Manchester United F.C. |accessdate=9 May 2014 }}</ref>\n|{{sort|06|$4.9B}}<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/malcolm-glazer/|title=Glazer family|work=Forbes|accessdate=4 September 2014}}</ref>\n|First Allied Corporation, [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]\n|-\n|[[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]<br />([[Newcastle United F.C.#Ownership|''more information'']])\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Mike Ashley (businessman)|Mike Ashley]]\n|{{sort|04|$2.8B}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/michael-ashley/|title=Michael Ashley|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-07-14}}</ref>\n|[[Sports Direct International]]\n|-\n|[[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]]<br />([[Norwich City F.C.#Ownership|''more information'']])\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Delia Smith]] and<br />{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Michael Wynn-Jones]] (53%)<br />{{flagicon|ENG}} Michael Foulger (15%)\n|{{sort|30|$30M}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.money.co.uk/misc/top-10-female-entrepreneurs.htm|title=Top 10 Female Entrepreneurs|work=Money|accessdate=9 May 2014}}</ref>\n|Food industry<br />Publishing<br />Poultry\n|-\n|[[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]\n|{{flagicon|KSA}} [[Abdullah bin Musa'ed bin Abdulaziz Al Saud|Abdullah bin Musa'ed]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2409663/Saudi-Prince-Abdullah-joint-owner-Sheffield-United.html | title=Fantasy football nut Saudi Prince Abdullah is joint owner of League One side Sheffield United | work=Daily Mail | accessdate=5 September 2013 | location=London | date=3 September 2013}}</ref>\n|{{sort|03|$255M}}\n|Saudi Paper Manufacturing Co.\n|-\n|[[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n|{{fla