 football team|Sweden Olympic]]\n|nationalcaps4  = 2\n|nationalgoals4 = 0\n|pcupdate       = 9 February 2020\n|ntupdate       =\n}}\n'''Valmir Berisha''' (born 6 June 1996) is a [[Swedes|Swedish]] professional [[footballer]] of [[Kosovo Albanians|Kosovar Albanian]] descent who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for Romanian club [[AFC Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te|Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Roma===\nHaving played for [[Halmstads BK]] as a youth, Berisha signed a 2.5-year contract with [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in January 2014.<ref>{{cite news|author=Matthew Scott|title=Valmir Berisha rejected Borussia Dortmund and Juventus to join Roma|url=http://www.goal.com/en-india/news/3753/germany/2014/02/02/4589305/roma-new-boy-berisha-reveals-dortmund-juventus-snubs|website=[[Goal.com]]|accessdate=25 March 2018|date=2 February 2014}}</ref> \n\n===Panathinaikos(loan)===\nHe joined [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] on loan during the 2014\u201315 season. He made his [[Superleague Greece|Superleague]] debut on 3 May 2015 against [[PAE Kerkyra]] replacing [[Nikos Karelis]] after 80 minutes in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/05/03/greece/super-league/pae-ao-kerkyra/panathinaikos-fc/1739619/|title=Kerkyra vs. Panathinaikos|publisher=Soccerway|date=3 May 2015|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Cambuur===\nIn July 2015, he again left Roma temporarily, moving to Dutch club [[SC Cambuur]] on loan for the 2015\u201316 with the option of a further season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Transfert: La Roma pr\u00eate encore Valmir Berisha|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transfert-la-roma-prete-encore-valmir-berisha/571756|accessdate=25 March 2018|work=L'\u00c9quipe|date=4 July 2015|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n===Aalesunds===\nAfter Cambuur, he moved to [[Aalesunds FK]] in 2017, but was loaned out to [[Ungmennaf\u00e9lagi\u00f0 Fj\u00f6lnir|Fj\u00f6lnir]] in 2018, where he stayed until his loan ended in January 2019.\n\n===Vele\u017e Mostar===\nOn 19 February 2019, Berisha signed for [[First League of the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina|First League FBiH]] club [[FK Vele\u017e Mostar]] on a 1 year contract with the possibility of an extension for one more year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/berisha-i-zvanicno-u-fk-velez/307179|title=Berisha i zvani\u010dno u FK Vele\u017e!|date=19 February 2019|accessdate=19 February 2019|language=Bosnian|author=A. Pa\u0161i\u0107|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref> He made his debut for Vele\u017e on 16 March 2019, in a 2\u20130 home league win against [[NK Jedinstvo Biha\u0107]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerway.com/matches/2019/03/16/bosnia-herzegovina/1st-league/fk-vele-mostar/nk-jedinstvo-bihac/2941052/|title=Vele\u017e Mostar vs Jedinstvo Biha\u0107|date=16 March 2019|accessdate=16 March 2019|language=English|website=us.soccerway.com}}</ref>\n\nHe scored his first goal for Vele\u017e on 27 April 2019, in a 4\u20130 home league win against [[FK Rudar Kakanj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/rodeni-briljirali-velez-razbio-rudar/316417|title=Ro\u0111eni briljirali: Vele\u017e razbio Rudar!|date=27 April 2019|accessdate=27 April 2019|language=Bosnian|author=S. Mla\u0107o|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref> On 25 May 2019, Berisha won the First League of FBiH with Vele\u017e after the club beat [[NK Bosna Visoko]] 0\u20132 away and got promoted to the [[Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/sport/nogomet/velez-se-nakon-tri-godine-vratio-u-premijer-ligu-bih/190525065|title=Vele\u017e se nakon tri godine vratio u Premijer ligu BiH|date=25 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|language=Bosnian|author=K.H.|publisher=Klix.ba}}</ref> He scored his first Premier League goal for Vele\u017e on 20 July 2019, in a 1\u20133 home loss against [[FK Mladost Doboj Kakanj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/beganovic-nadmudrio-rahimica-gorka-dobrodoslica-za-fk-velez-u-premijer-ligu/326672|title=Beganovi\u0107 nadmudrio Rahimi\u0107a: Gorka dobrodo\u0161lica za FK Vele\u017e u Premijer ligu|date=20 July 2019|accessdate=20 July 2019|language=Bosnian|author=S. Mla\u0107o|publisher=sportsport.ba}}</ref> Berisha left Vele\u017e in January 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/sport/nogomet/elmir-kuduzovic-i-valmir-berisha-napustili-velez/200120063|title=Elmir Kuduzovi\u0107 i Valmir Berisha napustili Vele\u017e|date=20 January 2020|accessdate=20 January 2020|language=Bosnian|author=D.B.|publisher=Klix.ba}}</ref>\n\n===Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te===\nOn 23 January 2020, Berisha signed a one-and-a-half-year contract with Romanian club [[AFC Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te|Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.afcchindiatargoviste.ro/stiri/seniori/391/bun-venit-diallo-i-berisha#.XkAcXI7VLGg|title=Bun venit, Diallo \u0219i Berisha!|accessdate=23 January 2020|date=23 January 2020|author=Mihaitalazarica|publisher=[[AFC Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te|Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te]]|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nBerisha was a member of the [[Sweden national under-17 football team|Swedish under-17 national team]] that finished third at the [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] and finished as the top scorer in the competition with seven goals.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{Updated|match played on 1 December 2019.}}<ref>{{Soccerway|id=270570|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club!!rowspan=2|Season!!colspan=3|League!!colspan=2|Cup!!colspan=2|Other!!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] (loan)||[[2014\u201315 Superleague Greece|2014\u201315]]||[[Superleague Greece]]\n|1||0||0||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[SC Cambuur|Cambuur]]||[[2015\u201316 Eredivisie|2015\u201316]]||[[Eredivisie]]\n|6||0||1||0||0||0||7||0\n|-\n|[[Aalesunds FK|Aalesund]]||[[2017 Eliteserien|2017]]||[[Eliteserien]]\n|23||0||2||0||0||0||25||0\n|-\n|[[Ungmennaf\u00e9lagi\u00f0 Fj\u00f6lnir|Fj\u00f6lnir]]||[[2018 \u00darvalsdeild|2018]]||[[\u00darvalsdeild karla (football)|\u00darvalsdeild]]\n|18||2||2||2||0||0||20||4\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[FK Vele\u017e Mostar|Vele\u017e Mostar]]||[[2018\u201319 First League of the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2018\u201319]]||[[First League of the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina|First League of FBiH]]\n|11||1||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||11||1\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2019\u201320]]||[[Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Premier League]]\n|9||1||2||2||colspan=2|\u2014||11||3\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!20||2||2||2||colspan=2|\u2014||22||4\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!67||4||7||4||0||0||74||8\n|}\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n<div>{{col-begin}}\n{{col-end}}\n</div>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Vele\u017e Mostar'''\n*[[First League of the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina|First League of FBiH]]: [[2018\u201319 First League of the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2018\u201319]]\n\n===Country===\n;Sweden U17\n* [[FIFA U-17 World Cup]] Third Place: [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup|2013]]\n\n===Individual===\n;International\n* [[FIFA U-17 World Cup]] Golden Boot: [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup|2013]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway}}\n\n{{AFC Chindia T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te squad}}\n{{FIFA U-17 World Cup awards}}\n{{Sweden men's football squad 2016 Summer Olympics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Berisha, Valmir}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Swedish footballers]]\n[[Category:Sweden youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Superleague Greece players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:\u00darvalsdeild players]]\n[[Category:Premier 